{"title":"State 4130 All-Road Hits Gravel Roads Raw With Exposed Steel Finish & Builds","link":"https://bikerumor.com/state-4130-all-road-hits-gravel-roads-raw-with-exposed-steel-finish-builds/","date":1699017868000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_headtube-finish.jpg\" alt=\"State Bicycle Co. 4130 All-Road Raw affordable steel gravel bike headbadge\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_headtube-finish.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_headtube-finish-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_headtube-finish-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_headtube-finish-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_headtube-finish-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_headtube-finish-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_headtube-finish-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>State Bicycle Co. gives their popular and affordable steel 4130 All-Road gravel bike a killer new no-finish, finish update – exposing the Raw steel of their frame and fork. Plus, this new build quietly gets an 11-speed drivetrain upgrade that means you’d be able to run a wider gearing spread. All that, and it still sells for less than $900. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, you can completely customize your individual build with 650b or 700c wheels, rigid or suspension forks, and plenty of optional accessories tailored to how you ride…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>State 4130 All-Road Raw affordable steel gravel bike</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_angled.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1150\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_angled.jpg\" alt=\"State Bicycle Co. 4130 All-Road Raw affordable steel gravel bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_angled.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_angled-297x190.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_angled-800x511.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_angled-120x77.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_angled-768x491.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_angled-1536x981.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/State Bicycle Co.)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s been more than 3 years since State Bicycle Co. jumped fully into gravel with their 4130 All-Road bike and own 1x 11-speed groupset. And it’s still one of the most affordable bikes to get into the gravel scene. Whether you’re looking for a fast gravel 700c or backcountry bikepacking adventure 650b build. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_riding.jpg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_riding.jpg\" alt=\"State 4130 All-Road Raw steel gravel bike, riding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_riding.jpg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_riding-297x186.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_riding-800x500.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_riding-120x75.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_riding-768x480.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Very little has changed with the 4130 All-Road. But don’t mess with what works, right?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, let’s just hit some gravel raw.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s new</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_details.jpg\"><img width=\"1350\" height=\"900\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_details.jpg\" alt=\"State 4130 All-Road Raw steel gravel bike, details\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_details.jpg 1350w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_details-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_details-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_details-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_details-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_details-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Probably the coolest new feature of this gravel bike is just its lack of paint. Every off-road cyclist loves a raw paintjob, am I right? But the 4130 All-Road Raw isn’t exactly raw steel. Instead, State have cleaned up the bike after welding and given it a phosphate conversion coating that does protect against corrosion before they brazed-on all the accessory mounts. It then gets a matte clear coat on top. But the bike will still eventually rust and “patina” over time.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_chainstay-detail.jpg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"750\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_chainstay-detail.jpg\" alt=\"State 4130 All-Road Raw steel gravel bike, brazed details\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_chainstay-detail.jpg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_chainstay-detail-297x174.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_chainstay-detail-800x469.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_chainstay-detail-120x70.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_chainstay-detail-768x450.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I personally think it’s pretty cool to see a bike sold this cheaply, reveal how much it is actually still worked by hand.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>New State All-Road 1 Derailleur 2.0</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_State-own-1x11-drivetrain.jpg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_State-own-1x11-drivetrain.jpg\" alt=\"State 4130 All-Road Raw versatile affordable steel gravel bike, 1x11 drivetrain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_State-own-1x11-drivetrain.jpg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_State-own-1x11-drivetrain-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_State-own-1x11-drivetrain-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_State-own-1x11-drivetrain-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_State-own-1x11-drivetrain-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_State-own-1x11-drivetrain-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/fancy-upgrades-to-state-4130-flat-bar-all-road-bike-plus-gravel-groupset-sneak-peeks/\" target=\"_blank\">flat bar gravel builds</a> we saw this spring, the Raw bike does also include the new upgraded State All-Road 1×11 derailleur that we got a teas of earlier this year. What’s new in v2.0 is a new internally adjustable clutch design. That gives cyclists the option to add more tension and more chain retention security for riding rougher off-road terrain. Or dial back the tension a bit for less drivetrain drag if you ride smoother terrain where retention is less an issue.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-All-Road-1-Rear-Derailleur-v2.jpg\"><img width=\"1350\" height=\"850\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-All-Road-1-Rear-Derailleur-v2.jpg\" alt=\"State Bicycle Co. All-Road 1 Rear Derailleur 2.0\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-All-Road-1-Rear-Derailleur-v2.jpg 1350w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-All-Road-1-Rear-Derailleur-v2-297x187.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-All-Road-1-Rear-Derailleur-v2-800x504.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-All-Road-1-Rear-Derailleur-v2-120x76.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-All-Road-1-Rear-Derailleur-v2-768x484.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>State Bicycle Co. All-Road 1 Rear Derailleur 2.0</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new State All-Road 1 Rear Derailleur 2.0 also features a slightly longer cage. That means you can now officially run up to a max 46-tooth on your 11-speed cassette. State still specs this 4130 All-Road Raw with an 11-42T cassette. But this drivetrain is directly compatible with SRAM 1:1 11-speed components, so a wider range cassette upgrade would be easy to find.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sadly, we’ll still have to wait for State’s own hydraulic dropbar brakeset, after they debuted <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/fancy-upgrades-to-state-4130-flat-bar-all-road-bike-plus-gravel-groupset-sneak-peeks/\" target=\"_blank\">their own hydro brakes</a> on the flat bar gravel builds.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech Details</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-angled.jpg\"><img width=\"1300\" height=\"900\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-angled.jpg\" alt=\"State Bicycle Co. 4130 All-Road Raw affordable steel gravel bike frameset angled\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-angled.jpg 1300w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-angled-297x206.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-angled-800x554.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-angled-120x83.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-angled-768x532.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All the rest of the technical details of this Raw bike are unchanged since the original versatile 4130 All-Road debut. Up to 700c x 45mm or 650b x 50mm tire clearance. 12mm thru-axles, flat mount disc brakes, 44mm headtube for straight or tapered steerers. A 68mm threaded bottom bracket, 27.2mm seatpost, and modular external cable routing. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset.jpg\"><img width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset.jpg\" alt=\"State Bicycle Co. 4130 All-Road Raw affordable steel gravel bike frameset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-Phosphate-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_frameset-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>You also get a couple of mounts for bottle cages, anything cages on the fork, rear rack mounts, and tabs for full coverage fenders front &amp; rear. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-gravel-bike-geometry.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-gravel-bike-geometry.jpg\" alt=\"State 4130 All-Road affordable steel gravel bike geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-gravel-bike-geometry.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-gravel-bike-geometry-297x149.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-gravel-bike-geometry-800x400.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-gravel-bike-geometry-120x60.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-gravel-bike-geometry-768x384.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-Co-4130-All-Road-Raw-gravel-bike-geometry-1536x768.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>All-Road Suspension Fork option?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-lock-out-and-air-e1695751749207.jpg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"674\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-lock-out-and-air-e1695751749207.jpg\" alt=\"State Bicycle All Road Suspension Fork lock out and air\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-lock-out-and-air-e1695751749207.jpg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-lock-out-and-air-e1695751749207-297x156.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-lock-out-and-air-e1695751749207-800x421.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-lock-out-and-air-e1695751749207-120x63.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-lock-out-and-air-e1695751749207-768x404.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another new possibility in custom builds is State’s own new <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/state-bicycle-co-gravel-suspension-fork/\" target=\"_blank\">All-Road Suspension Fork</a> that launched just over a month ago. Offering 40mm of front wheel travel, State claims it weighs only 1600g . Interestingly, that could be as little as 100-200g heavier than the low-cost steel unicrown fork that comes standard on the 4130 All-Road.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-laying-down.jpg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"721\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-laying-down-edited.jpg\" alt=\"State Bicycle All Road Suspension Fork laying down\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-laying-down-edited.jpg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-laying-down-edited-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-laying-down-edited-800x451.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-laying-down-edited-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-laying-down-edited-768x433.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-Bicycle-All-Road-Suspension-Fork-laying-down-edited-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Plus, you actually save a hundred bucks off retail when buying the new suspension fork with a complete State bike. Get one for $350 extra when you buy the State 4130 All-Road Raw.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>State 4130 All-Road Raw – Pricing, options &amp; availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_650b-adventure-build.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_650b-adventure-build.jpg\" alt=\"State 4130 All-Road Raw versatile affordable steel gravel bike, adventure bikepacking 650b\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_650b-adventure-build.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_650b-adventure-build-297x165.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_650b-adventure-build-800x444.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_650b-adventure-build-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_650b-adventure-build-768x427.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_650b-adventure-build-1536x853.jpg 1536w\" /></a><figcaption>State Bicycle Co. 4130 All-Road Raw 650b</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Raw finish is available now in4 frames sizes (XS-L) and complete bike builds starting at $899.99. For that, you get State’s own updated 1x 11-speed drivetrain. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_700c-fast-gravel-build.jpg\"><img width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_700c-fast-gravel-build.jpg\" alt=\"State 4130 All-Road Raw versatile affordable steel gravel bike, fast gravel 700c\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_700c-fast-gravel-build.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_700c-fast-gravel-build-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_700c-fast-gravel-build-800x480.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_700c-fast-gravel-build-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_700c-fast-gravel-build-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>State Bicycle Co. 4130 All-Road Raw 700c</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And you get to pick from 2 sizes of alloy wheels. 650b wheels with knobby 2.1″ Vittoria <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/vittoria-claims-big-performance-gains-with-graphene-2-0-tires/\" target=\"_blank\">Barzo</a> mountain bike tires. Or 700c wheels with fast-rolling 38mm Vittoria <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/soc18-vittoria-terreno-zero-gravel-tire-debuts-w-carbon-wheels-plus-air-liner-mtb-insert/\" target=\"_blank\">Terreno Zero</a> semi-slick gravel bike tires.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_ready-to-ride.jpg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_ready-to-ride.jpg\" alt=\"State 4130 All-Road Raw versatile affordable steel gravel bike, adventure-ready\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_ready-to-ride.jpg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_ready-to-ride-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_ready-to-ride-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_ready-to-ride-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_ready-to-ride-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/State-4130-All-Road-Raw-affordable-steel-gravel-bike_ready-to-ride-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Technically, the 4130 All-Road Raw is also available as a $430 frameset. But it sold out before we even saw it was offered. Fingers crossed that State might bring it back in the future.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.statebicycle.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>StateBicycle.com</em></a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/state-4130-all-road-hits-gravel-roads-raw-with-exposed-steel-finish-builds/\">State 4130 All-Road Hits Gravel Roads Raw With Exposed Steel Finish &amp; Builds &lt;$900</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"1e7a83cbf825b4e2f1ec784c69d48a8c0956a78141b0eaeee7d4c5659701f514","category":"Cycling"}